5. Conclusions
The present investigation has examined structural and catalytic properties of numerous chromia/zirco- nia, chromia/g-alumina and chromia/silica catalysts,covering a wide range of Cr concentration. This study allows some nal conclusion to be drawn:(i) several Cr species are present on the surface of the investigated catalysts in amounts depending on the specific support and Cr concentration.
(ii) the dehydrogenation activity per total Cr atom is substantially higher for zirconia-based catalysts than for g-alumina- and silica-based ones.
(iii) a proportionality is found between activity and high-oxidation state Cr, thus indicating the in- Fig. 13. Dehydrogenation rate per total Cr atom at 773 K as a function of the fraction of the high oxidation state chromium.
